This issue is raised from: [https://support.atlassian.com/browse/JSP-50687]:

{quote}
To achieve our goal of displaying issues based on their component, we could not rely on your documentation which describes what should be in context: http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Contents+of+the+Velocity+Context . This documentation says that projectManager is always in context if you use version 3.4 or higher. This was not correct. And when you look at the documentation for the object, com.atlassian.jira.project.ProjectManager, it says that most of the functionality has been deprecated in V4.0 and that you should use com.atlassian.jira.bc.project.component.ProjectComponentManager instead. Although this is stated, it does not appear that a variable for this object is in context either. I also found that the components variable, which is supposed to always be present since version 3.4, was not in context either.
{quote}

