I like the roadmap view, because you can see what is scheduled for the upcoming versions and  gives you an overview about the progress of them.

But I think, layout of the issue list could be optimized, so that it looks more like at other places in JIRA.

I don't understand, why you use such a small font since. Also I don't understand, why "UNRESOLVED" is bold (it is not bold in issue navigator) and why the resolution like Fixed or Duplicate is converted to uppercase.

