When I did the following 
{noformat}
{code}
if (exclusiveAccess) {
  col = getDelegator().findAllCache(userEntity, order);
} else {
  col = getDelegator().findAll(userEntity, order);
}
{code}
{noformat}
It added carriage returns where I don't expect them (after the "if" and after the "else").

It looks like it may work in this Description Field:
{code}
if (exclusiveAccess) {
  col = getDelegator().findAllCache(userEntity, order);
} else {
  col = getDelegator().findAll(userEntity, order);
}
{code}

When sending a request directly through HTTP there is no validation for new line in the summary field. For instance:

{noformat}
curl "http://<url>/secure/CreateIssueDetails.jspa?pid=...&issuetype=...&summary=My+other%0D%0Atest+issue&description=Test%0D%0Adescription&os_username=...&os_password=..."
{noformat}

Note that the summary has a new line encoded as %0D%0A. The issue is created, and it contains a new line. To prove this, you can edit the created issue, save it without changes, and check the issue history.

